2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of two parameters in the IEEE 802.15.6 standard based on actual measurements. Information Theory deals with the quantification, storage, and communication of information, which is relevant to this aspect of the paper. 

3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a reliable and efficient system for WBAN based on the IEEE 802.15.6 standard. Systems and Control deals with the analysis, design, and control of complex systems, which is relevant to the system proposed in this paper. 

4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper involves the implementation of a WBAN prototype system, which may involve hardware components. Hardware Architecture deals with the design and analysis of computer hardware, which is relevant to the implementation aspect of this paper.
